# Cloudflare Pages routing for the grudgeDot launcher.
# Order matters — most-specific first, SPA catch-all LAST.

# Root: gated hub with login + service preview cards.
# After login, the cards link into the SPA (which is served by the catch-all below).
# Targets MUST NOT include the `.html` suffix or Cloudflare Pages' automatic
# pretty-URL canonicalizer will 308-redirect `/portal.html` -> `/portal`,
# which then re-matches the `/portal` rewrite and produces an infinite loop.
/             /portal      200
/launcher     /portal      200
/hub          /portal      200
# Direct access to the React SPA shell, bypassing the hub.
/app          /           200
/app/*        /           200

# API proxying is handled by `functions/api/[[path]].ts` (a Cloudflare Pages
# Function), NOT by `_redirects`. Pages silently drops `200` rewrites whose
# destination is an external URL, so the rules that used to live here
# (auth -> id.grudge-studio.com, /api/* -> api.grudge-studio.com,
#  Discord -> grudgewarlords.com) never actually proxied; every /api/* call
# fell through to the SPA fallback below and returned index.html.
# The Pages Function now owns all /api/* routing.

# Admin is a separate static HTML page; preserve direct hits.
# Use the pretty URL `/admin` (no .html) so Pages' canonicalizer doesn't loop.
/admin        /admin       200

# SPA fallback — must be last so it doesn't shadow the rules above.
# Rewrite to `/` (which Pages serves as `index.html`) instead of explicit `/index.html`.
/*            /            200
